<HEADLINE>
FT  08 APR 93 / Cuomo shuns court
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GEORGE GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GOVERNOR Mario Cuomo of New York has taken himself out of consideration for
nomination to the US Supreme Court, according to news reports yesterday,
writes George Graham.
Mr Cuomo, who has long been an eloquent social conscience for the Democratic
party, had been viewed as the front-runner to replace Justice Byron White,
who will retire from the court in the summer.
President Bill Clinton refused to discuss the Supreme Court appointment
yesterday, but said he thought Mr Cuomo was 'terrific'.
During the presidential election campaign last year, Mr Clinton had said he
thought the New York governor would make a good Supreme Court justice, and
Mr Cuomo himself has said the position would be heaven. In his usual
ambivalent style, though, he also likened the court to a tomb.
</TEXT>
