<HEADLINE>
FT  07 APR 93 / International Company News: Royal Oak Mines joins
environment battle
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By BERNARD SIMON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TORONTO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ROYAL Oak Mines, the aggressive Canadian gold producer, has bought control
of Geddes Resources, a small exploration company which is engaged in a
high-profile battle with environmentalists over plans to build a large
copper and gold mine in northern British Columbia.
Royal Oak will pay CDollars 10m (USDollars 7.9m) for the 39 per cent stake
in Geddes currently held by Northgate Exploration.
Royal Oak said the acquisition 'has significant upside potential and limited
downside risk'. The deposit is estimated to contain 300m tonnes of copper
ore with a grade of 1.38 per cent, as well as substantial quantities of
gold, silver and cobalt.
The British Columbia provincial government has come under strong pressure
from environmental groups in the US and Canada to turn down Geddes'
application.
The environmentalists contend that the mine will do incalculable damage to
the Tatshenshini River and the surrounding region, which is widely regarded
as one of most scenic wilderness areas on the continent.
Should the project not go ahead, Royal Oak is banking on suitable
compensation.
</TEXT>
