<HEADLINE>
FT  07 APR 93 / UK Company News: Headlam acquisition and cash call
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Headlam Group, the floor coverings and fabrics distribution group, is
raising Pounds 5.1m through a 1-for-4 rights issue at 92p to finance part of
the cost of its acquisition of Shulman &amp; Sons, a Glasgow-based floor
coverings distributor.
The group also announced a jump in 1992 pre-tax profits from Pounds 304,000
to Pounds 1.11m, in accordance with FRS 3. Earnings per share came through
at 3.85p (2.21p) and the proposed final dividend is 1.85p for an increased
total of 2.6p (2.4p). Turnover was Pounds 58.8m (Pounds 21.7m).
Consideration for Shulman is about Pounds 2.1m, to be satisfied in a mixture
of shares, cash and loan notes.
The rights issue, of up to 5.88m new shares, will be underwritten by Robert
Fleming and brokers are Albert E Sharp.
