FT  07 APR 93 / West Midlands signals upturn
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
COMPANIES in the west Midlands are indicating that the long-awaited economic
recovery could be under way.
A survey of more than 700 companies by the West Midlands Group of Chambers
of Commerce paints the brightest picture for many months, with a marked rise
in orders and deliveries from manufacturers and improved trade for service
companies.
Manufacturers saw a 13 per cent increase in home orders and an 8 per cent
rise in export orders in the last quarter compared with the previous three
months. Service companies reported home orders rising 9 per cent and export
orders increasing 11 per cent. Companies in both sectors expect to see their
turnover increase.
