<HEADLINE>
FT  07 APR 93 / Pilot blamed for North Sea crash
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE CRASH of a North Sea helicopter with the loss of 11 lives in March last
year was caused by pilot error, Sheriff Alexander Jessop ruled yesterday in
Aberdeen. But he said Shell, the oil company, probably contributed to the
deaths of some people who survived the crash but later drowned.
The Tiger helicopter, operated by Bristows, plunged into the sea seconds
after taking off in very bad weather conditions from Shell's Cormorant Alpha
platform.
The sheriff said Shell had ignored statutory regulations demanding that a
standby vessel be informed when helicopter flights were to take place.
Shell Expro yesterday said it had taken steps immediately after the accident
to rectify its procedures.
