<HEADLINE>
FT  07 APR 93 / Postponement to Clinton economic package allows Senate to
clear up critical piece of legislation
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Agreement to postpone President Bill Clinton's Dollars 16bn economic
stimulus package allowed the Senate to clear up one critical piece of
legislation that had been held up by the Republican filibuster: a measure to
raise the legal ceiling on US federal debt to Dollars 4,370bn.
The US Treasury, which had been forced to delay debt sales to avoid
breaching the previous ceiling of Dollars 4,145bn, yesterday held a Dollars
14.25bn sale of 52-week bills and announced another Dollars 22.4bn auction
of 13 and 26-week bills for today.
</TEXT>
