<HEADLINE>
FT  06 APR 93 / London Stock Exchange: Mirror improves
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The market liked the confident statement from Mirror Group enough to
discount the company's 1992 pre-tax loss of Pounds 84m. The newspaper
group's shares rose 11 to 115p on heavy turnover of 10m.
Analysts had anticipated the heavy exceptional charge and turned their
attention to the rise in operational profits. They were also heartened by
improvement in advertising revenues. Ms Lorna Tilbian of SG Warburg
increased her 1993 forecast by 50 per cent to Pounds 60.9m and said:
'Despite the recent rise in the share price, the fundamentals have improved
sufficiently to enable us to maintain a buy recommendation.'
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Mirror Group Newspapers.
</CO>
